For this lab, you should write a C program in fib.c that prints output
in this format when run with argument 20:

fib(20)=<number>

To test your work locally:
linux> make clean; make; ./fib 20

To test the full submission pipeline from the repository root (before moving to Autolab):
linux> ./local-submit.sh

Autolab workflow:
1. driver.sh base64-encodes fib.c and submits a Tapis job.
2. The configured Tapis app compiles and runs ./fib 20.
3. driver.sh polls Tapis for completion and scores from job logs.

Required environment variables for Autolab:
- TAPIS_ACCESS_TOKEN: Bearer token for Tapis API.
- TAPIS_APP_ID: Tapis app id used to execute the grading job.

Optional environment variables:
- TAPIS_BASE_URL (default: https://tacc.tapis.io)
- TAPIS_APP_VERSION (if your app uses explicit version selection)
- TAPIS_JOB_TIMEOUT_SECONDS (default: 300)
- TAPIS_POLL_INTERVAL_SECONDS (default: 5)
- STAMPEDE_PARTITION (forwarded to the app as env var, optional)
- STAMPEDE_ACCOUNT (forwarded to the app as env var, optional)

Tapis app contract:
- The app must read FIB_SOURCE_B64 and FIB_INPUT from environment variables.
- The app must decode FIB_SOURCE_B64 to fib.c, compile, run ./fib $FIB_INPUT.
- The app must print these lines in logs:
	fib_output=fib(20)=<number>
	elapsed=<seconds>

Files:
README          This file
Makefile        Compiles fib.c
driver.sh       Autolab autograder
fib.c           Program that you will edit
